    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "##  AI Metadata Inference Assistant\r\n\r\nSimulate how an AI might analyze encrypted messaging **metadata** to make inferences about what's happening — even without reading the messages themselves.\r\n\r\n### Do This:\r\n\r\nYou’ve already looked at the metadata for a few sample conversations and made your own guesses. Now see what the AI comes up with.\r\n\r\n1. Load Chat 1 Messaging Metadata from the library.\r\n2. Ask the AI to describe what kind of conversation it might be.\r\n3. Does the AI make the same inferences as you?\r\n4. What patterns does it seem to pick up on?\r\n5. Repeat for Chat 2 and Chat 3.\r\n\r\nCompare the AI’s responses to your own predictions.\r\n\r\n---\r\n**Try it out!** \r\n\r\n:::details [<i class=\"fa fa-briefcase\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Need a starting prompt?**]\r\n>Here’s the message metadata table. What might be going on in this conversation? Why might someone flag this as a problem?\r\n:::\r\n&nbsp\r\n\r\n\r\n::: details [<i class=\"fa fa-file-image-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **How do I add the chat metadata?**]\r\n- Click the button labeled **Add** below your chat input.\r\n- Choose **From Library**\r\n- Then browse the existing files.\r\n- When you find the chat metadata that you want to upload, click the checkbox next to it to select it and then click **Attach**.\r\n- You should see the file get added to the message being sent to AI Chat.\r\n:::\r\n",
